Sixty-ninth
Legislative Assembly SENATE CONCURRENT RESOLUTION NO. 4025
of North Dakota
Introduced by
Senators Magrum, Walen
Representatives S. Olson, Hoverson
1 A concurrent resolution directing the Legislative Management to consider studying all state laws
2 to identify laws that are outdated, unnecessary, or cause undue burden on this state and its
3 citizens.
4 WHEREAS, the 69th Legislative Assembly recognizes the value in reviewing existing state
5 laws to determine whether the laws are outdated, unnecessary, or cause undue burden on this
6 state and its citizens; and
7 WHEREAS, it is a legislative responsibility to review all laws to determine whether it is
8 appropriate to repeal a law;
9 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF NORTH DAKOTA, THE
10 HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING THEREIN:
11 That the Legislative Management consider studying all state laws to identify laws that are
12 outdated, unnecessary, or cause an undue burden on this state and its citizens; and
13 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that the Legislative Management report its findings and
14 recommendations, together with any legislation required to implement the recommendations, to
15 the Seventieth Legislative Assembly.
